<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Corpse" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Corpse</orth> (unchanged in the plural: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 43</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.192" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 192</bibl>), dead body: <bibl n="shak. tn 2.4.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 4, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 2, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.132" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.266" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 266</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 62</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 3.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. III, 1, 64</bibl>. <cit><quote>dead c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 43</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 105</bibl>. == the body without the soul: <cit><quote>my lord your son had only but the c., but shadows and the shows of men, to fight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.192" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 192</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Incorpsed</emph>).
